quizzes.textContent:
[h1]if...else Statements[/h1]

An [b]if[/b] statement can be followed by an optional [b]else [/b]statement, which executes when the condition evaluates to false. 
[b]For example:[/b][code format="java" codeId="728"]int age = 30;

[b]if[/b] (age < 16) {
   System.out.println("Too Young");
} [b]else [/b]{ 
   System.out.println("Welcome!");
}
//Outputs "Welcome"[/code]
[note]As age equals 30, the condition in the [b]if[/b] statement evaluates to false and the [b]else [/b]statement is executed.[/note]
